HEADWORD: Terebratula
<hw>Ter`e*brat"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Terebratulae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Nl.,
dim. fr. <ets>terebratus</ets>, p. p., perforated.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of brachiopods which includes many
living and some fossil species. The larger valve has a perforated beak,
through which projects a short peduncle for attachment. Called also
<altname>lamp shell</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Terebratulid</ent>⟦br⟧
